                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "Lee, 31",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "The biggest decision I’ve ever made was when I decided to move out of my parents’ house. I was pretty scared at first, to be honest. But I soon found an apartment in the same town with a couple of friends. Thinking about it now, it was the right time for me to make the change from living at home to living with friends."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "Maki, 25",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "Three years ago, I decided to climb El Capitan in Yosemite National Park. It was always one of those things on my bucket list. Since I started to put the plan into action, I’ve learned a lot about climbing and myself. My advice? Never lose heart! If you are working toward a goal, you’ll achieve it in the end. I haven’t gone to Yosemite yet, but I know I will!"
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                  "paragraphImage": "",
                  "paragraphTitle": "Alessandra, 35",
                  "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "When I was a teenager, I wanted to be a famous movie star. But it didn’t happen. My dream now is to be a chef. I’ve learned that the best way to turn a dream into reality is to be realistic. Set short-term goals to help you stay motivated. Becoming a chef is going to be difficult, but I’ve already started a course and cook regularly for friends and family."
                  ]
                }
